A 35-year-old man been arrested after reports of a stabbing at a nightclub. One man was taken to hospital with non-life threatening injuries from the Fiction nightclub in Swansea city centre. South Wales Police said the attack was reported at 02:30 GMT on Saturday, and armed officers attended the scene. The 35-year-old, from Townhill, Swansea, was arrested on suspicion of assault, police said. He remains in custody "We are not looking for anyone else in relation to this matter and a weapon has been seized," said Det David Connick.